//// Fixture-driven tests for `glugify/anchor`, generated from the
//// github-slugger test suite (test/fixtures.json) so the anchors
//// produced here are exactly GitHub's. The fixtures are stateful:
//// they run in order through a single `Anchorer`, so repeated
//// headings exercise the duplicate counter.
////
//// Omitted fixtures: the synthetic Unicode-category sweeps whose
//// expected output keeps characters introduced after Unicode 7.0
//// (Letter, Mark, Number and friends), plus "Unassigned". Erlang/OTP
//// <= 27 bundles a regex engine with Unicode 7.0 tables, so those
//// fixtures test the engine version rather than the algorithm: OTP 28
//// and JavaScript pass them, OTP 27 strips e.g. Osage or Adlam
//// letters. The realistic fixtures and the removal-direction sweeps
//// are stable across engines and are all kept.

